---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { LorenzoComment } from '../components/LorenzoComment';
const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Agents Party?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Agents Party is an interactive web-based tool to visually configure and export Agent Orchestration systems. It uses a D&D-inspired theme to help you assemble a 'Party' of specialized AI agents for platforms like Gemini and Claude."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does the 3-tier architecture work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The framework follows a hierarchical structure: The Throne Room (Meta-Level) for strategy, The GM Session (Coordinator) for project management, and The Party (Sub-Agents) for execution."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What AI platforms are supported?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Agents Party currently supports tailored exports for Google Gemini (Experimental Subagents), Anthropic Claude (Agent Teams), and OpenAI (Codex Multi-Agent)."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is my data private?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Entirely client-side logic ensures no data leaves your browser. Your party configurations and templates are generated locally."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I enable experimental features for Gemini or Claude?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For Gemini, enable 'enableAgents' in your settings. For Claude, run your quest with the '--team' flag to switch to a fully collaborative Agent Team model."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<Layout 
  title="Agents Party | The Compendium"
  description="Master the art of agent orchestration. Explore the roles, rules, and hierarchical levels of the Agents Party framework."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <main class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden text-ink-deep">
    <!-- Decorative Background Element -->
    <div
      class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-full max-w-6xl aspect-square bg-gold-600/5 blur-[120px] rounded-full -z-10"
    >
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 relative">
      <!-- Navigation -->
      <nav
        class="flex justify-between items-center mb-16 bg-parchment-base border-[3px] border-ink-deep p-4 shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] rounded-sm"
      >
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 group">
          <img
            src="/images/logo-sm.png"
            alt="Agents Party"
            class="w-10 h-10 group-hover:-translate-y-0.5 group-hover:scale-105 transition-all object-contain rendering-pixelated"
            style="image-rendering: pixelated;"
          />
          <span
            class="font-black tracking-widest text-ink-deep uppercase text-sm group-hover:text-crimson transition-colors font-mono"
            >Agents Party</span
          >
        </a>
        <div
          class="hidden md:flex gap-8 text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-deep font-mono items-center"
        >
          <a
            href="/compendium"
            class="hover:text-crimson hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-transform"
            >Compendium</a
          >
          <a
            href="https://github.com/kelset/agent-party-planner"
            class="hover:text-crimson hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-transform flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"
              ><path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg
            >
            GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Content -->
      <article
        class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-h3:text-ink-deep prose-p:text-ink-faded prose-strong:text-ink-deep"
      >
        <h1 class="sr-only">Agents Party Compendium: Agent Orchestration Guide</h1>
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-parchment-light mb-8 tracking-widest uppercase drop-shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] font-mono"
        >
          The Compendium
        </h2>

        <p
          class="text-xl text-ink-deep font-bold mb-12 leading-relaxed bg-parchment p-6 border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] rounded-sm relative text-center"
        >
          The <strong>Agents Party</strong> is an interactive web tool that lets you
          visually configure and export <em>Agent Orchestration</em> packages. Using
          a fantasy RPG inspired theme, you can assemble a "Party" of specialized
          AI agents, customize their personalities, and download a ready-to-use orchestration
          setup tailored for platforms like Gemini or Claude. All entirely in your
          browser.
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-2xl font-black text-parchment-light mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest border-b-[3px] border-ink-deep/50 pb-2 font-mono"
        >
          The Multi-Tier Architecture
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-deep font-bold mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-crimson pl-4">
          The Agents Party framework uses a structured 3-tier hierarchy: The Throne Room (Meta-Level) 
          for high-level strategy, The GM Session (Coordinator) for autonomous project management, 
          and The Party (Sub-Agents) for specialized technical execution.
        </p>
        <LorenzoComment class="mb-12">
          The exported packages follow a strict 3-tier hierarchy that separates
          meta-planning<br class="hidden md:block" /> from actual coding. This ensures
          privacy, reduces clutter, and maintains clear roles.
        </LorenzoComment>

        <div class="space-y-8 mb-16">
          <section
            class="bg-parchment-base p-6 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] relative overflow-hidden"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none"
              style={{
                backgroundImage:
                  'linear-gradient(to right, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(to bottom, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px)',
                backgroundSize: '16px 16px',
              }}
            >
            </div>
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-black text-ink-deep mb-3 flex items-center gap-3 font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              <span
                class="text-gold-600 drop-shadow-[1px_1px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >I.</span
              > The Throne Room <span
                class="text-sm font-bold text-ink-faded tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Meta-Level)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-faded font-bold relative z-10">
              The strategic layer where you interact with meta-agents to define
              the quest, set constraints, and adjust rules mid-flight. It runs
              in an isolated directory to keep your main codebase clean.
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside text-ink-faded font-bold mt-4 space-y-2 relative z-10"
            >
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">The Game Creator:</strong> The architect
                and your primary brainstorming partner.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">The Master of Spies:</strong> The real-time
                analyst, critiquing orchestration inefficiencies.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">The Bard:</strong> The chronicler who
                translates technical achievements into an engaging narrative recap.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section
            class="bg-parchment-base p-6 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] relative overflow-hidden"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none"
              style={{
                backgroundImage:
                  'linear-gradient(to right, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(to bottom, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px)',
                backgroundSize: '16px 16px',
              }}
            >
            </div>
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-black text-ink-deep mb-3 flex items-center gap-3 font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              <span
                class="text-gold-600 drop-shadow-[1px_1px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >II.</span
              > The GM Session <span
                class="text-sm font-bold text-ink-faded tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Coordinator)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-faded font-bold relative z-10">
              The Game Master (GM) runs inside the actual codebase. It acts as
              the project manager&mdash;reading journals, evaluating results,
              and spawning the correct Party Members to do the work. The GM
              coordinates but <em>never</em> writes code or runs tests itself.
            </p>
            <h4
              class="text-sm font-black text-ink-deep mt-8 mb-2 uppercase tracking-widest font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              Standard Quest Lifecycle
            </h4>

            <div
              class="relative pl-8 space-y-8 before:absolute before:inset-y-0 before:left-[11px] before:w-[3px] before:bg-ink-deep mt-6 pb-4 relative z-10 font-bold"
            >
              <!-- Phase 1 -->
              <div class="relative">
                <div
                  class="absolute -left-[39px] -top-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-sm bg-parchment border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] flex items-center justify-center"
                >
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-sm bg-emerald-500"></span>
                </div>
                <h5
                  class="text-ink-deep font-black mb-2 tracking-widest uppercase text-sm font-mono"
                >
                  Phase 1: Recon
                </h5>
                <div
                  class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">🏹</span>
                    <div class="text-ink-faded">
                      <strong class="text-emerald-600 font-black tracking-wide"
                        >Ranger</strong
                      > gathers baseline measurements and maps the environment.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">🧙‍♂️</span>
                    <div class="text-ink-faded">
                      <strong class="text-purple-600 font-black tracking-wide"
                        >Wizard</strong
                      > analyzes the data and writes a structured attack plan.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!-- Phase 2 -->
              <div class="relative">
                <div
                  class="absolute -left-[39px] -top-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-sm bg-parchment border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] flex items-center justify-center"
                >
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-sm bg-crimson"></span>
                </div>
                <h5
                  class="text-ink-deep font-black mb-2 tracking-widest uppercase text-sm font-mono"
                >
                  Phase 2: Execution <span
                    class="text-ink-faded text-xs normal-case"
                    >(Iterative Loop)</span
                  >
                </h5>
                <div
                  class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">⚔️</span>
                    <div class="text-ink-faded">
                      <strong class="text-crimson font-black tracking-wide"
                        >Warrior</strong
                      > implements the specific changes according to the plan.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 pl-4 text-ink-light">
                    <svg
                      class="w-4 h-4 stroke-[3px]"
                      fill="none"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      ><path
                        stroke-linecap="square"
                        stroke-linejoin="miter"
                        d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15"
                      ></path></svg
                    >
                    <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-black"
                      >Loop until approved</span
                    >
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">🧛‍♂️</span>
                    <div class="text-ink-faded">
                      <strong class="text-purple-800 font-black tracking-wide"
                        >Warlock</strong
                      > scrutinizes the code. Blocks bad changes or approves.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div
                    class="mt-2 pt-3 border-t-[3px] border-ink-deep/20 flex flex-col gap-3"
                  >
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                      <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">🧙‍♂️</span>
                      <div class="text-ink-faded">
                        <strong class="text-purple-600 font-black tracking-wide"
                          >Wizard</strong
                        > &amp; <strong
                          class="text-emerald-600 font-black tracking-wide"
                          >Ranger</strong
                        > verify the final outcome matches the plan and metrics.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 opacity-80">
                      <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">🧑‍⚕️</span>
                      <div class="text-ink-faded">
                        <em>If blockers hit:</em>
                        <strong class="text-cyan-700 font-black tracking-wide"
                          >Healer</strong
                        > diagnoses and recovers the environment.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!-- Phase 3 -->
              <div class="relative">
                <div
                  class="absolute -left-[39px] -top-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-sm bg-parchment border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] flex items-center justify-center"
                >
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-sm bg-gold-400"></span>
                </div>
                <h5
                  class="text-ink-deep font-black mb-2 tracking-widest uppercase text-sm font-mono"
                >
                  Phase 3: Document & Report
                </h5>
                <div
                  class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep flex items-start gap-3 text-sm shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >
                  <span class="text-xl drop-shadow-sm">📜</span>
                  <div class="text-ink-faded">
                    The GM records final measurements, writes the summary log,
                    and reports back to the Throne Room.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <LorenzoComment class="mt-8 mb-2">
              Of course, this standard lifecycle is just the default baseline.
              You can and should adapt it to fit the unique needs and
              composition of your specific party!
            </LorenzoComment>
          </section>

          <section
            class="bg-parchment-base p-6 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] relative overflow-hidden"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none"
              style={{
                backgroundImage:
                  'linear-gradient(to right, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(to bottom, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px)',
                backgroundSize: '16px 16px',
              }}
            >
            </div>
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-black text-ink-deep mb-3 flex items-center gap-3 font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              <span
                class="text-gold-600 drop-shadow-[1px_1px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >III.</span
              > The Party <span
                class="text-sm font-bold text-ink-faded tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Sub-Agents)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-faded font-bold mb-4 relative z-10">
              The specialized workers executing the tasks. The magic lies in
              their <strong>constructive tension</strong>: they are not yes-men,
              but experts who push back on bad plans and scrutinize each other's
              work.
            </p>
            <div
              class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm relative z-10 font-bold"
            >
              <div
                class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
              >
                <strong
                  class="text-emerald-600 block mb-1 font-black tracking-widest uppercase font-mono"
                  >🏹 Ranger (Telemetry)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-ink-faded"
                  >Data gatherer. No ego, just numbers.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
              >
                <strong
                  class="text-purple-600 block mb-1 font-black tracking-widest uppercase font-mono"
                  >🧙‍♂️ Wizard (Strategist)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-ink-faded"
                  >Creates ambitious attack plans.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
              >
                <strong
                  class="text-crimson block mb-1 font-black tracking-widest uppercase font-mono"
                  >⚔️ Warrior (Implementation)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-ink-faded"
                  >Pragmatic shipper. Writes the code.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
              >
                <strong
                  class="text-purple-800 block mb-1 font-black tracking-widest uppercase font-mono"
                  >🧛‍♂️ Warlock (Code Review)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-ink-faded"
                  >Adversarial critic. Blocks bad code.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-parchment p-4 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[2px_2px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] md:col-span-2"
              >
                <strong
                  class="text-cyan-700 block mb-1 font-black tracking-widest uppercase font-mono"
                  >🧑‍⚕️ Healer (Diagnostics)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-ink-faded"
                  >Systematic fixer and environment recovery.</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section
            class="bg-parchment-base p-6 rounded-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] relative overflow-hidden"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none"
              style={{
                backgroundImage:
                  'linear-gradient(to right, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(to bottom, #2c1e16 1px, transparent 1px)',
                backgroundSize: '16px 16px',
              }}
            >
            </div>
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-black text-ink-deep mb-3 flex items-center gap-3 font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              <span
                class="text-gold-600 drop-shadow-[1px_1px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)]"
                >IV.</span
              > The Agentic Mindset <span
                class="text-sm font-bold text-ink-faded tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Best Practices)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-faded font-bold mb-4 relative z-10">
              The default presets are a culmination of custom ideas, ongoing
              trends in the broader agent ecosystem, and recent additions
              inspired by <a
                href="https://simonwillison.net/guides/agentic-engineering-patterns/"
                class="text-crimson hover:underline"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Simon Willison's <em>Agentic Engineering Patterns</em></a
              >. The system enforces strict behavioral guidelines to prevent
              "vibe coding" and AI hallucinations:
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside text-ink-faded font-bold mt-4 space-y-2 relative z-10"
            >
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">Red/Green TDD:</strong> The Warrior is
                strictly instructed to write a failing test <em>first</em> before
                implementing any code. The Warlock will reject pull requests without
                tests.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">Context Minimization:</strong> The GM
                isolates sub-agents, passing them <em>only</em> the specific chunk
                of the plan they need to know, preventing prompt confusion.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-crimson">Aggressive Branching:</strong> Because
                writing code is cheap, the Party is encouraged to spin up multiple
                git branches to test different approaches simultaneously.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <LorenzoComment class="mt-8 mb-2">
            <h4
              class="text-sm font-black text-crimson mb-2 uppercase tracking-widest font-mono relative z-10"
            >
              ⚠️ Experimental Gotchas
            </h4>
            <p class="font-bold text-sm relative z-10">
              To fully unlock the "true" parallel multi-agent potential of these
              tools, you need to enable their experimental flags:
              <br /><br />
              - <a
                href="https://geminicli.com/docs/core/subagents/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-crimson hover:underline"
                ><strong>Gemini (Subagents)</strong></a
              >: Set <code
                >"experimental": &#123; "enableAgents": true &#125;</code
              > in your global settings to natively route to our <code
                >.gemini/agents/</code
              > files.<br />
              - <a
                href="https://developers.openai.com/codex/multi-agent"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-crimson hover:underline"
                ><strong>Codex (Multi-Agent)</strong></a
              >: Ensure <code>multi_agent = true</code> is toggled via <code
                >/experimental</code
              > so it reads our <code>.codex/config.toml</code>.<br />
              - <a
                href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/agents-and-tools/claude-code/overview#agent-teams"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-crimson hover:underline"
                ><strong>Claude (Agent Teams)</strong></a
              >: Simply run the quest with the <code>--team</code> flag to switch
              from hub-and-spoke subagents to a fully collaborative Agent Team.
            </p>
          </LorenzoComment>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-16 text-center">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-block px-10 py-4 bg-crimson hover:bg-crimson-hover text-white font-black rounded-sm shadow-[4px_4px_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] transition-all uppercase tracking-widest text-sm border-[3px] border-ink-deep active:translate-y-[4px] active:translate-x-[4px] active:shadow-[0_0_0_var(--color-ink-deep)] font-mono"
        >
          Assemble Your Party
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer
      class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 mt-8 border-t-[3px] border-ink-deep/30 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-6 text-ink-deep text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest font-mono"
    >
      <span>© 2026 Agents Party</span>
      <div class="flex gap-8 text-center md:text-left">
